Vol / Page: 174
Edition:
Quote: Deterioration of the value of stock, by the unrestricted grazing of "scabby sheep," Mr. Stafford, and every other flock owner is aware of, and demand an act of legislation to prevent; and yet that gentleman entails upon others a similar evil, which he could abolish with but slight inconvenience, and is in justice bound to suffer no longer to exist.
